Why is mercantilism chosen? The author of the passage chose mercantilism as the economic system to discuss because it was the dominant economic system of the time.

Why is mercantilism employed by companies? Mercantilism is employed by companies because it is a system that believes in the accumulation of wealth. Mercantilism is a system where countries restrict the amount of goods that are imported and exported in order to increase the amount of money that is in the country. This system was used a lot in the 1700s and 1800s.

Why do countries hide their companies from the free market? There can be a number of reasons why a country might choose to hide its companies from the free market. One reason might be to protect the companies from competition. Another reason might be to keep the companies from being taken over by foreign companies.
Does free trade concentrate costs? Yes, free trade can concentrate costs by transferring production to countries with lower wages and environmental standards.
Does free trade disperse benefits? The benefits of free trade are dispersed among the people who participate in the trade.
